    <h2>Is It Safe to Pay Utility Bills Through Apps?</h2>
    <p>Yes — completely safe. JazzCash, Easypaisa, and all major bank apps are regulated by the State Bank of Pakistan and use bank-grade encryption. Your payment goes directly to the utility company's account. Always use the official app from Google Play or App Store — never use third-party bill payment apps that are not affiliated with your bank or a licensed fintech.</p>

    <h2>What If My Payment Does Not Reflect on the Bill?</h2>
    <p>Online payments typically reflect within 2 to 4 hours. If your bill still shows unpaid after 24 hours, call your utility's helpline with your transaction ID from the payment confirmation SMS. All banks and mobile wallets provide a transaction ID as proof of payment. Your utility must accept this as valid payment evidence.</p>

